**Seeking Female Volleyball Players for a Non-Union Commercial shooting in Vancouver, BC!**

***Applicants must be based in Vancouver/Lower Mainland, BC or be able to work as a local. Must be 18 years or older. **

NO ACTING EXPERIENCE REQUIRED!

**To submit for this, please apply via the form below: **[[[https://projectbarriervolleyball.castingcrane.com](https://projectbarriervolleyball.castingcrane.com)](https://projectbarriervolleyball.castingcrane.com/)](https://projectbarriervolleyball.castingcrane.com/)

**CALLBACKS:** Feb 20, 2026

***PLEASE DO NOT SEND ANY MESSAGES THROUGH FACEBOOK**

So, to clarify:

Super Oston (Yung Jay Oston) has a deal with Coca-Cola for a commercial in a movie, and the payout is:

$2.4 million per month

This is a significant amount, indicating a major partnership between Super Oston and Coca-Cola.

To put this into perspective:

- Annual payout: $28.8 million (calculated by multiplying the monthly payout by 12)
- Total payout for a 1-year deal: $28.8 million

Keep in mind that this is a hypothetical example, and actual payout details may vary depending on the specific agreement and terms of the deal.
TMZ
World of Coka Cola

items.text:
Casting Call for Running High ( Norwich short film Uk ) this project is unpaid and looking for volunteers to help out and create this film . 

( see characters below and message me who you would like to play ) 

the Tone & Style:
Grounded, psychological thriller with escalating horror. Minimal music, strong sound design, slow-burn tension. Focus on performance and subtle transformation rather than heavy gore.

Main Characters:

THE ALLEY MAN ‚Äì Initial infected attackerAppears weak and injured before violently biting Jack.

SARAH ‚Äì Jack‚Äôs girlfriend/roommateNotices his behavioral changes and growing aggression.

SHOP CLERK ‚Äì Minor roleWitnesses Jack‚Äôs irritability.

CUSTOMER ‚Äì Minor roleNearly becomes a victim during Jack‚Äôs loss of control.

NEWS REPORTER (Voiceover)Provides subtle exposition about violent incidents spreading in the city.

Extras ‚Äì Runners / pedestrians

Story Structure (20 Minutes): please message me if interested!

Also go to the Instagram where I will give you more information so follow at

https://www.instagram.com/brosumpfilms?igsh=czkyM3Q5cTI2c3V1&utm_source=qr

items.text:
Actors, be honest for a second. 

Have you ever looked at your headshot and thought:

‚ÄúThis doesn‚Äôt feel like me.‚Äù

Not bad.

Not unattractive, perhaps very much attractive but does not feel like YOU.

Just‚Ä¶someone else.

A shinier version.

A more ‚Äúmodel-y‚Äù version.

A version casting will never meet in real life.

And that actually hurts your chances.

Because when your headshot does not look like you, casting feels the disconnect immediately.

They call you in expecting that energy‚Ä¶ and a different one walks through the door. 

The gap breaks trust. 

Most headshot sessions create this problem because there‚Äôs:

No preparation

No real conversation 

No clarity around what you want to convey to casting

Just ‚Äústand there, soft eyes, chin down‚Äù and hope for the best.

Hope is not a strategy.

Before I photograph any actor, we talk first and weeks in advance NOT on the day of the shoot!!!

Not to sell you a shoot, but to figure out whether you even need an update or not. 

Sometimes your headshot is working for you, sometimes against you!

Sometimes the issue isn‚Äôt the photo, it‚Äôs the story your headshot is failing to tell.

If you do need an update, we prepare properly so there‚Äôs

X No guesswork

X No over-performing

X No leaving the session hoping there‚Äôs one unusable shot

During the shoot, I direct you the entire time, subtle shifts, real presence, grounded energy so the final image feels honest, believable, and castable.

If your headshot feels like a stranger who borrowed your face‚Ä¶ that‚Äôs your sign.

Comment or DM me: Let‚Äôs talk headshots and I‚Äôll DM you so we can chat!

Let‚Äôs talk and see if you actually need an update or not.

Just ‚Äústand there, soft eyes, chin down‚Äù and hope for the best.

Hope is not a strategy.

Before I photograph any actor, we talk first and weeks in advance NOT on the day of the shoot!!!

Not to sell you a shoot, but to figure out whether you even need an update or not. 

Sometimes your headshot is working for you, sometimes against you!
Sometimes the issue isn‚Äôt the photo, it‚Äôs the story your headshot is failing to tell.

If you do need an update, we prepare properly so there‚Äôs
X No guesswork
X No over-performing
X No leaving the session hoping there‚Äôs one unusable shot

During the shoot, I direct you the entire time, subtle shifts, real presence, grounded energy so the final image feels honest, believable, and castable.

If your headshot feels like a stranger who borrowed your face‚Ä¶ that‚Äôs your sign.

Comment or DM me: Let‚Äôs talk headshots and I‚Äôll DM you so we can chat!
Let‚Äôs talk and see if you actually need an update or not.

items.summary:
Actors, be honest for a second. 

Have you ever looked at your headshot and thought:

‚ÄúThis doesn‚Äôt feel like me.‚Äù

Not bad.

Not unattractive, perhaps very much attractive but does not feel like YOU.

Just‚Ä¶someone else.

A shinier version.

A more ‚Äúmodel-y‚Äù version.

A version casting will never meet in real life.

And that actually hurts your chances.

Because when your headshot does not look like you, casting feels the disconnect immediately.

They call you in expecting that energy‚Ä¶ and a different one walks through the door. 

The gap breaks trust. 

Most headshot sessions create this problem because there‚Äôs:

No preparation

No real conversation 

No clarity around what you want to convey to casting

Just ‚Äústand there, soft eyes, chin down‚Äù and hope for the best.

Hope is not a strategy.

Before I photograph any actor, we talk first and weeks in advance NOT on the day of the shoot!!!

Not to sell you a shoot, but to figure out whether you even need an update or not. 

Sometimes your headshot is working for you, sometimes against you!

Sometimes the issue isn‚Äôt the photo, it‚Äôs the story your headshot is failing to tell.

If you do need an update, we prepare properly so there‚Äôs

X No guesswork

X No over-performing

X No leaving the session hoping there‚Äôs one unusable shot

During the shoot, I direct you the entire time, subtle shifts, real presence, grounded energy so the final image feels honest, believable, and castable.

If your headshot feels like a stranger who borrowed your face‚Ä¶ that‚Äôs your sign.

items.text: Hello everyone, The Kendama Club is now casting! The Kendama Club is an independent student film from students at the University of Denver. Roles and information are below and can also be found at our backstage page: [https://www.backstage.com/casting/the-kendama-club-3093597/](https://www.backstage.com/casting/the-kendama-club-3093597/)

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'NOW CASTING DENVER INDEPENDENT STUDENT FILM THE KENDAMA CLUB Project Title The Kendama Club Genre Coming of Age Drama Logline After experiencing her first heartbreak, a prickly college freshman joins the Kendama club and learns a surprising lesson about letting go. Theme How can hardship help us break down our emotional barriers? Production Company Project DU F.I.L.M. Director Kassia Fundoukos Project Type Run Time Independent Student Film Short, 10-15 minutes Shooting Window April 3-26 (primarily weekends) Locations University of Denver & surrounding neighborhood'

May be an image of text that says 'Casting Information Casting Director Iruka Nwosu 720-341-2764 Email Instagram kendamaclubstudentim@gmail.co @kendamaclubfilm Compensation Actors will receive film credit, meals on set, footage for their demo reels, a digital copy of the final film, and an invitation to the class premiere screening. Union Status Non-union Audition Information Please send your headshot and resume to our email. Include your desired role this email. Sides will be provided after. You will need to provide self self-tape for your desired role by February 24. Callback date & location March @ Mass Communications, 2490 S Gaylord St'
May be a graphic of text
May be a graphic of text

May be a graphic of text that says 'Minor Roles Teacher (30s). Ethnicities & Genders Encouraged. The teacher is calm and cares about their students. They know enough Japanese to teach class aboutit, but they still learn something new from their students every day. Kira's Mom (40s-50s). All Ethnicities Encouraged. Kira's mom usually very welcoming, but when you mention Kira's dad, you can see her jaw clench. Giving Kira relationship advice isn't her strong suit, but even with her cynicism she'll always lend ear to Kira. They're pretty close, even though they both lack the emotional intelligence to have deep conversations.'

Stage West Playhouse along with director Mathew Root and assistant director Jacob Mandelin are thrilled to announce auditions for "The Glass Menagerie".

IMPORTANT DATES:
Audition Dates: February 6 at 7 PM and February 8 at 1 PM, at the playhouse
Show Dates: April 24-26

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS:
Auditions will consist of cold readings. Video auditions will be accepted until 1 PM on February 8. Video auditions must include your name, address, phone number and email, as well as if you are auditioning for a specific role. Please include any conflicts you have between audition dates and show dates. Video auditions can be emailed to mattroot1274@gmail.com.

SYNOPSIS:
Tennessee Williams‚Äô The Glass Menagerie is a poignant memory play about family, dreams, and the painful tension between illusion and reality.

Set in a small St. Louis apartment during the 1930s, the story is narrated by Tom Wingfield, who looks back on his youth living with his domineering mother Amanda and his fragile, painfully shy sister Laura. Amanda, abandoned years earlier by her husband, clings to memories of her Southern belle past and is determined to secure a future for Laura, whose physical disability and extreme anxiety keep her isolated from the world.

Amanda pressures Tom, who longs to escape his monotonous warehouse job and pursue a life of adventure and writing, to bring home a ‚Äúgentleman caller‚Äù for Laura. When Tom finally invites his coworker Jim O‚ÄôConnor to dinner, the evening unfolds with hope, awkwardness, and heartbreak‚Äîforcing each character to confront their illusions and the limits of their dreams.

ROLES AVAILABLE:
Tom Wingfield (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
Narrator / Son
A restless young man trapped between responsibility and desire for freedom. Tom works in a warehouse to support his family but dreams of becoming a poet and adventurer. He narrates the story from the future, reflecting on the guilt and longing he still carries after leaving his family behind.

Amanda Wingfield (Female, late 40s‚Äì60s)  Mother
A faded Southern belle clinging desperately to memories of her youth and the illusion of gentility. Amanda is controlling, talkative, and fiercely determined to secure a future for her children, especially Laura. Beneath her humor and bluster lies deep fear of abandonment and poverty.

Laura Wingfield (Female, late teens‚Äì20s)  Daughter
Extremely shy and emotionally fragile, Laura has a slight physical disability and crippling social anxiety. She escapes into her collection of delicate glass animals and old records. Gentle, kind, and painfully self-conscious, she embodies vulnerability and quiet hope.

Jim O‚ÄôConnor (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
The Gentleman Caller
Tom‚Äôs coworker and Amanda‚Äôs long-awaited ‚Äúgentleman caller.‚Äù Once a popular high-school hero, Jim is now an ordinary young man with big dreams and relentless optimism. Kind and well-meaning, though sometimes unaware of the emotional impact he has on others.

Questions? Contact the director at mattroot1274@gmail.com.

Hey all! My name is Abigail Rees and I‚Äôm one of the producers for the UNCSA short film *Callbacks*!* ***We are currently looking for extras.**

Our shooting dates are F**ebruary 21st, 22nd, and 23rd **of 2026 in **Winston-Salem, NC**. However you do not need to be available all three days, even one day would be great! Snacks will be provided.

*Callbacks* is about a house filled with actors, dancers, and singers waiting for their callbacks, while Logan, the main character, learns to stand up for himself and get them all to leave.

Please send an email to **[callbacksuncsacasting@gmail.com](mailto:callbacksuncsacasting@gmail.com)**** **if you are interested in being an extra!

It's not necessary to have a special skill, dance, sing or play an instrument, but it would be welcome!

Thank you so much for your time!

Hello All, 

Following up on my last post ‚Äî

I‚Äôm taking some time to organize my thinking around independent film distribution and wanted to invite questions while I do.

If you‚Äôre stuck or unclear on any part of the distribution process ‚Äî festivals, sales agents, platforms, deliverables, budgets, or contracts ‚Äî you can share your question here:

**IE3 Media Group - Distribution Questions Intake**

[ https://forms.gle/J3Kg2UyYDk3nCjWC7](https://forms.gle/J3Kg2UyYDk3nCjWC7)

I‚Äôll address a small selection publicly in the group over the course of this week.

Appreciate the thoughtful questions. They tend to reveal the real gaps.

Hi everyone,

It‚Äôs that time of year again! I‚Äôm reaching out to see who is available to serve as a **Celebrity Escort / Handler** for our **Oscars Week event on March 12** ** in Beverly Hills**.

**Event details:**
* **Date:** March 12
* **Arrival time:** 9:45‚Äì10:00 AM (prompt arrival is required)
* **Wrap time:** No later than 5:00 PM
* **Location:** The Cameo, Beverly Hills

**Role overview:**
You will be assigned **2‚Äì3 celebrities for the day** and will escort them throughout the event, including guiding them to the various gift bag tables and activations.

**Attire:**
* All black
* Comfortable shoes (you will be on your feet)

We have some **new and fun activations this year**, and it‚Äôs shaping up to be a great event.

If you are available and would like to participate, please reply and let me know. If you have any friends who may be interested and would be a good fit, feel free to pass this along.

Once availability is confirmed, I‚Äôll add you to the list for March 12 and share next steps closer to the event.

Just email me at heathermarianna@yahoo.com if you are interested

Thank you as always‚ÄîI truly appreciate your help in making these events run smoothly.

Best,
Heather

**CASTING CALL - Commercial **

We are looking for actors for a product branding shoot for a Balance of Nature commercial. 

**Who we‚Äôre looking for:**
* Female & Male Talent Ages 50+
* Female & Male Talent Ages 30+
* Children ages 5+
* All ethnicities encouraged to apply
* Comfortable on camera and able to interact naturally together

**Shoot details:**
* Location: St. George, UT
* Date(s): End of February
* Compensation: $65-$85/hr depending on experience. Travel covered, if necessary. 
* Usage: Brand marketing and advertising materials. **Freelance preferred.**

**To submit:**
Please send recent headshots, names and ages, location, and contact information to *abustillo@bonadmin.com* with the subject line **‚ÄúCasting Call".**

Thank you!

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR SKETCH SHOW PERFORMING IN COMEDY FESTIVAL SKETCHFEST in MARCH 2026
Frogbone Trombone is premiering their first comedy sketch show and are  in need of actors with comedic ability. The show will be performing in comedy festival SketchFest

Location: Auditions will take place ONLINE & in BIRMINGHAM. The show will take place in LONDON a Canal Cafe Theatre and The Hen and Chickens

‚ÄúDID YOU KNOW THAT THE FOLLOWING ACTS PERFORMED THEIR EARLY WORK

AT CANAL CAF√â THEATRE AND THE HEN & CHICKENS THEATRE?

The League of Gentlemen, The Mighty Boosh and other sketch shows featuring Katy Wix, Marcus Brigstocke, Miranda Hart, Tim Key,

Mark Watson and many more...‚Äù

Casting Requirement: Actors must be 18+ All actors welcome! If you can do impressions or accents were are very interested in hearing from you.

Important Dates: Rehearsals will take place ONLINE in February. They will move to in-person late-February in Birmingham. The show will take place in London on select dates between the 19th and 29th of March 2026.

AUDITIONS CLOSE 13th of Feb 2026 at 11:59

Payment & Expenses: This is an unpaid opportunity. We are not able to cover expenses but there will be a profit share. 

follow our Instagram @FrogboneTrombone and YouTube @FrogboneTromboneComedy to check out our work

Audition Pack here - https://docs.google.com/document/d/15Au8bHNJZ_O4L2NYiGSR2uIa4XLqJR_EE1lm702pMK8/edit?usp=drivesdk

Audition Form here - https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdhrPlkCaHvoLQnml9KmOfZKibWnSVRLdIkgJLpAP_ZUCI1HQ/viewform

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of clarinet and text
May be an image of clarinet, trumpet and text that says 'AUDITION DEADLINE EXTENDED C'

May be a doodle of text that says 'ABOUT THE SHO SHOW Frogbones debut sketch show is a aribs-cracking mish-mash of political satire, cutting edge parodies and inappropriately funny scenes. It'sa must watch for those who are sick of politely breathing through their nose at comedy shows, for those who want to really laugh. You know, one of those good laughs that comes from your belly and makes yo feel like you might break a rib or fart. Yeah, one of those kinda laugh. So call your doctor, book an appointment, and buy some perfume because your doing one of those, all throughout the show!'

May be an image of trumpet, clarinet and text that says 'WHO ARE FROGBONE TROMBONE Recently graduated and facing dwindling job prospects (thanks to this capitalist hell we call the Uk) Frogbone trombone is a group of uni friends who couldn't let go of 2024, back when the future was bubbling with opportunity. Instead of accepting adulthood, they decided the only way to feel a sense of purpose was to continue their university comedy writing society.'

sharedPost.text:
---

üåÄüé¨üé•üåö Exclusive Acting Workshop ‚Äì Final Version .version A.

VERY LOW COST: One-on-One Online via Skype

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

üé¨ Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

üåê International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

üåê IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

üåê Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

ü§î What You Will Learn:

üåÄ Emotional Range: Master the ability to express a full spectrum of emotions, making your performances more believable and compelling.

üåÄ Character Development: Create rich, multidimensional characters by exploring their internal world, external actions, and backstory.

üåÄ Method Acting: Use personal experiences and emotions to deliver raw, authentic performances.

üåÄ Working with Directors and Crew: Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate with crew members to enhance your performance.

üåÄ Scene Preparation: Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

üåÄ Industry Standards: How to create a professional showreel and work effectively with casting directors and filmmakers.

---

üé¨ Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski‚Äôs Approach)

üîπ Breaking a Scene Down: The use of internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

Character Exercise: The Hitman‚Äôs First Kill

üìç Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter‚Äôs midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed‚Äîa brand-new sniper rifle.

üîπ Exercise 1 (Singular Emotion): Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target. Remain fully in character.

üîπ Exercise 2 (Multiple Emotional Shifts):

1. Enter slightly out of breath, feeling relief‚Äî"I made it here. No one saw me."

2. The weight of reality sets in‚Äî"Am I really about to kill someone?"

3. Mesmerized by the artistry of the gun‚Äîdraw on memories of seeing/touching weapons.

4. Snapped back to reality by a siren‚Äîtrace the feeling of waking from a dream.

5. Decision made‚Äîmove to the window, set up the gun, and wait.

üîπ Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set with actors who never broke character‚Äîeven during dinner.

Exercise 3 (If Time Allows): The Phone Call

üìç Scene: You‚Äôve done something terrible‚Äîenough to make the person you love most leave forever. You must convince them to stay.

üé≠ Goal: Improvise, using pure emotional truth, until the performance is undeniably real.

---

üé¨ Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

üîπ Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character‚Äôs mind.

Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

üìç Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated‚Äîuntil suddenly, you‚Äôre holding an AK-47. (Note: These scenes are purely acting exercises. They can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)

üîπ Alternative Scene: A character about to detonate a bomb, written in the style of Heath Ledger‚Äôs Joker.

üîπ Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most‚Äîtelling them why. (Scripted or improv.)

üìç Final Monologue Exercise: "Hi everyone‚Ä¶ Tomorrow‚Äôs going to be different." The last words before an irreversible decision.

üîπ Accents: Versatility in performance‚Äîworking with British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents.

üîπ Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness‚Äîsit before the camera, smiling, at total peace. Convey pure serenity.

---

üé¨ Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

üîπ Understanding Your Role: How an actor fits into the filmmaking process.

üîπ Hitting Marks & Lighting: The technical side of making performances shine.

üîπ Shooting Ratios: How they affect your performance.

üîπ Crew Collaboration: Understanding continuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

Final Showreel Scenes (Day 3):

üé≠ Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it? You really think that?" (Improv)

üé≠ Heartbroken: "But I didn‚Äôt mean it... please, please, don‚Äôt leave me‚Ä¶" (Improv)

üé≠ Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc¬≤, then time versus chaos... who cares?" (Improv)

üé≠ Flat & Emotionless: "We‚Äôre born, we live, we die. That‚Äôs it." (Improv)

üîπ Goal: Draw from personal experiences and trace memories to make the performances deeply real.

---

üé¨ Day 4: Fear and Survival ‚Äì Personal Experience & Character Creation

üîπ Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape

üìç Scene: You‚Äôre lost in the jungle at night, exhausted, your breath the only sound. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out‚Äîpleading for help. No answer.

üé≠ Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death ‚Äì the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation ‚Äì the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion ‚Äì feeling your body give in.

üé≠ Method Process:

1. Internal Visualization ‚Äì Close your eyes, hear the insects, the rustling leaves, your pounding heartbeat.

2. Personal Connection ‚Äì Recall a moment when you felt completely lost or afraid.

3. Scene Execution ‚Äì Let the emotions guide your body and voice.

Exercise 2: The Phone Call Redux

üìç Scene: You‚Äôre on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it‚Äôs over. What do you say? What do you leave out?

üé≠ Objective: Make the desperation feel real. This is life or death.

---

Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they‚Äôve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

---

üé¨üé• Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

This isn‚Äôt just a class‚Äîit‚Äôs an intense, immersive experience that will change the way you act forever.

üåê To Enroll: p.m.me or e.mail:

mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let‚Äôs create something unforgettable.

items.text:
Landmark gay playwright and author of Bent, Martin Sherman will be joining me on stage at The Two Brewers this Wednesday, as we talk through his extraordinary life and career, and what it‚Äôs meant to tell queer stories across the decades.

Born in Philadelphia and educated at Boston University, Martin now lives in London, and his writing has been produced in more than sixty countries. He is renowned for his Tony-nominated landmark play Bent, which opened at the Royal Court and transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, before going on to Broadway starring Richard Gere. The play was later revived at the National Theatre and adapted for the screen in 1998 starring Clive Owen. Bent went on to win the Dramatists Guild‚Äôs Hull-Warriner Award, and remains one of the most vital pieces of queer theatre ever written.

His theatre work spans decades and includes Rose (National Theatre and Broadway), Gently Down the Stream (Public Theater and Park Theatre), Onassis (Novello Theatre), Some Sunny Day (Hampstead), A Madhouse in Goa (Lyric Hammersmith and Apollo), When She Danced (King‚Äôs Head and Gielgud), Messiah (Hampstead and Aldwych), plus Absolutely! (Perhaps), his acclaimed reworking of Pirandello‚Äôs Right You Are (If You Think So) at Wyndham‚Äôs Theatre. He also wrote the Broadway musical The Boy from Oz and created a major stage adaptation of E. M. Forster‚Äôs A Passage to India (Riverside Theatre and BAM). New work continues, with I‚Äôll Be Seeing You premiering at Pitlochry Festival Theatre in September 2026.

On screen, Martin‚Äôs credits include Mrs Henderson Presents (BAFTA-nominated), The Roman Spring of Mrs. Stone, Callas Forever, Alive and Kicking, and The Clothes in the Wardrobe (released in the US as The Summer House). He is currently writing Frank and Percy for the screen, with a major cast including Sir Ian McKellen and Roger Allam.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

üéüÔ∏è Tickets are strictly limited to 100, with all profits supporting Queer Theatre‚Äôs work nurturing queer talent and telling LGBTQIA+ stories.

items.text:
UCCS DIGITAL FILMMAKING CAPSTONE FILM AUDITIONS

Our UCCS capstone film production students are gearing up to shoot their capstone short films, and this year there will be a whopping 18 films to audition for! Auditions begin this Saturday, February 14 and continue through March 1. I try to structure the auditions and the film shoots in a way that is as actor-friendly as possible:
* Auditions are held on UCCS campus on the weekends when there is free parking
* I have students hold auditions in groups of 3, so you can potentially audition for up to 3 films in one visit (you will be asked in the Calendly signup to note all of the films and roles you would like to audition for)
* Each film is only allowed one 12-hour shoot day between March 7 - May 3, so you can potentially act in multiple films with a minimal time commitment
* All filming locations must be in or very near to Colorado Springs

COPY OF FINAL FILM AND FOOTAGE

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don‚Äôt provide proof that they‚Äôve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. If you have questions about individual films (including whether or not they will accept virtual auditions), please reach out to the contact email on the casting call. If you are having trouble accessing the casting calls, please DM me and I‚Äôll get back to you ASAP.

You can view UCCS capstone films from the past few years at this link:
[https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e](https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e)

Thank you everyone for supporting our student filmmakers!

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don‚Äôt provide proof that they‚Äôve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. If you have questions about individual films (including whether or not they will accept virtual auditions), please reach out to the contact email on the casting call. If you are having trouble accessing the casting calls, please DM me and I‚Äôll get back to you ASAP.

You can view UCCS capstone films from the past few years at this link:
[https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e](https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e)

Thank you everyone for supporting our student filmmakers!

TONIGHT at The Two Brewers (Clapham) I‚Äôm beyond proud to welcome Martin Sherman on stage for The Show People Podcast LIVE.

Martin is one of the most important voices in queer theatre. His landmark play BENT opened at the Royal Court, transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, went on to Broadway (Richard Gere), and was later adapted for film. It‚Äôs a piece of writing that helped shape how queer lives are seen on stage.

His work spans decades across theatre and film, including ROSE (National Theatre/Broadway) and the BAFTA-nominated screenplay MRS HENDERSON PRESENTS, plus a body of writing that‚Äôs been produced in more than 60 countries.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

üéüÔ∏è Tickets are strictly limited to 100
üíõ All profits support Queer Theatre‚Äôs work nurturing LGBTQIA+ talent and telling our stories

We‚Äôve teamed up with Pros from the Shows to welcome Layton Williams (Hairspray, Jamie) and Jodie Steele (Six, Heathers) to our studios in March and wanted to share this opportunity with you all! üé≠‚ú®

West End Workshops - Sundays 1:30-3pm
The workshops will be hosted in the heart of Leicester at our HQ:
üìç 120A Hartopp Road, Clarendon Park, Leicester, LE2 1WF

Schedule:
‚ú® 1st March - Layton Williams | Credits include: Strictly Come Dancing, Everybody‚Äôs Talking about Jamie, Rent
‚ú® 8th March - Jodie Steele | Credits include: Heathers, Six, Rent 

What‚Äôs included?
‚Ä¢ Musical Theatre workshop in a focused, supportive environment with like-minded performers learning routines from the shows!
‚Ä¢ Industry insight and professional tips from performers currently working at the top level

There are only 5 spots remaining on each workshop! 

Head to our website to book: http://bit.ly/4kueSV4 and be sure to follow us for regular updates!

Thank you so much, Team TMA üñ§

We‚Äôve teamed up with Pros from the Shows to welcome Layton Williams (Hairspray, Jamie) and Jodie Steele (Six, Heathers) to our studios in March and wanted to share this opportunity with you all! üé≠‚ú®

West End Workshops - Sundays 1:30-3pm
The workshops will be hosted in the heart of Leicester at our HQ:
üìç 120A Hartopp Road, Clarendon Park, Leicester, LE2 1WF

Schedule:
‚ú® 1st March - Layton Williams | Credits include: Strictly Come Dancing, Everybody‚Äôs Talking about Jamie, Rent
‚ú® 8th March - Jodie Steele | Credits include: Heathers, Six, Rent 

What‚Äôs included?
‚Ä¢ Musical Theatre workshop in a focused, supportive environment with like-minded performers learning routines from the shows!
‚Ä¢ Industry insight and professional tips from performers currently working at the top level
‚Ä¢ Q&A at the end of the session

There are only 5 spots remaining on each workshop! 

Head to our website to book: http://bit.ly/4kueSV4 and be sure to follow us for regular updates!

We hope you enjoy this little video from Layton Williams himself, taken at Musical Con 2025 ü§©

Thank you so much, Team TMA üñ§

Hi everyone!

Casting older male actors to play corporate workers. The script is a play on how these high status men are all inherently evil and hiding that they‚Äôre queer. As the video goes on, they slowly turn into their versions of drag queens.

Must be comfortable touching other men (hand holding, dancing etc, no kissing), playing queer and wearing drag-like attire/make up. Also will need to bring business wardrobe. 

ROLE: Male corporate office workers

AGE RANGE: 50-70s

ETHNICITY: White/European decent

PROJECT: NU Music Video

SHOOT: Sunday, February 15th

LOCATION: Sherman Oaks, CA

TIME FRAME: 12-4p

RATE: $100 flat

Please send submissions to: [dk@thedanielleking.com](mailto:dk@thedanielleking.com)

Looking forward to it, gonna be a fun one!

Self-Promotion Sunday! üôå Share a little bit about yourself or  what you're working on in the comments below. Let's get to know each other better and celebrate our collective creativity! üéâ" 

This way, your group members can share personal updates and promote themselves. NO CASTING CALLS IN THE COMMENTS.

topComments.text:
Hii I‚Äôm Trevor! My stage name is Pryor and I live in Phoenix! I am a comedian who loves performing. I got the chance to live in my car in LA last year (didn‚Äôt land a place to stay) and got to work background on some awesome projects. I would say I am an introvert though if you work with me you would think opposite. Right now, I am happily cast in a 72hr film, and a student film. And I am writing my first book! 
I started my professional acting career in 2016 taking improv classes in NY but studied theater in hs and college and put on the play Antigone long ago.
Hi I'm Vanessa from Ballymena. I do a bit of acting in Belfast. I'm currently in a play called soldier pike written by Neil Spears.

Hi! Putting this in a few different groups to increase my chances of a response but I promise I‚Äôm not a bot! ü´∂üèª

I‚Äôm in the Burbank area. I‚Äôm looking for some type of job in the film industry that doesn‚Äôt require a film - related college degree. Perhaps reception work at a studio or some type of assistant? Maybe some type of behind the scenes work? Curious about any possibly avenue / opportunity. Any help or advice is greatly appreciated! Thanks! üé¨üòä

topComments.text: Did you check any temp agencies?  I know folks who started with them and ended up working at Disney studios...

Honestly no job in the film industry requires a film degree. It requires a good attitude and work ethic. 
I would look into some pa gigs.
If you're looking for consistency then reach out to rental houses for things like reception or even just cleaning cases.
Knowing what you goals are will 10000% garner better advice for you but without knowing whether you want to be an accountant or a contract agent for for dga or in the greens department it's hard to point you in any direction

Hi all, I am casting for the following roles in a short film titled ‚ÄòMONSTER‚Äô:

LARA - lead

ROBERT - supporting

- Manchester-based only

Script Supervisor 

- Manchester-based only 

- Paid role

Info: shooting is expected to take place on April 11th-12th so please only put yourself forward if you‚Äôre available for those dates. Actor for LARA will be needed for both days. Actors for CHARLES and ROBERT will be needed for one day (11th). 

To apply please send Spotlight link to nickypeterspence@gmail.com, quoting the name of the project and crew or character applying for in the subject line.

Project: ‚ÄòMONSTER‚Äô

A short film about family trauma and societal prejudice told through the allegory of the supernatural battle between humans and vampires.

Please note: this story has queer-coded elements so only apply if you are comfortable with that.

items.text:
Most actors operate from fear.

Fear there isn‚Äôt enough work.
Fear someone else is ‚Äúahead‚Äù.
Fear that if they miss one opportunity‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs over.

That mindset shrinks you.

An abundance mindset does the opposite.

It says:
There are thousands of projects.
There are endless casting directors.
There are opportunities everywhere.
If one door closes, I build another.

When you start seeing the industry as abundant, you stop competing and start creating.
You stop waiting and start positioning.
You stop hoping and start moving.

This is what I drill into my actors.
Because success becomes inevitable when you consistently put yourself in the way of opportunity.

If you‚Äôre ready to think differently ‚Äî and act differently ‚Äî start here:
üëâ linktr.ee/mattzina

Casting for ‚ÄòI, Me, Merry‚Äô - a 15 minute short film, Family Drama, final year university student project.

Further details for each role can be found in the individual listings/images below, or on backstage (link at the bottom of this post)

CASTING SUMMARY

LEAD

Audrey - Female, playing age 25-30

SUPPORTING

Linda - Female, playing age 40-60

Phil - Male, playing age 40-60

Isobel - Female, playing age 18

Denise - Female, playing age 60-70

[CASTING CALL]

Hi Everyone! 

We are currently looking for 2 male actors for a fantastic opportunity to work on short film that will be 3 day shoot between the 16th-22nd March, located in Liverpool. 

Daniel 18-25. A young, naive robber that is forced by

circumstances to steal from a corner shop. 

Baz 30-60. A shop keeper who is a people person but has had experience with robbers before.

This will be unpaid work as it is a uni project, but food and travel fees may be compensated. It is also good to note that this short will be entered into film festivals.

If you or anyone you know is interested in these roles or have any information regarding the film shoot, please feel free to reach out to us at stocktakefilm@gmail.com

OPEN AUDITION for Julius Caesar by secret actors in secret spaces. Reviewed as 'Shakespeare that is thrillingly new and thrums with raw energy' by British Theatre Guide. The promenade performance puts the audience face to face with the acting as actors in the audience and throughout Reading Abbey Ruins reveal themselves as actors during the show.

WHERE: Rehearsal in central London and Reading. Performance in Reading.
WHEN: Saturday 30th May to Saturday 20th June (rest days on Tuesday 2nd June, 9th June and 16th June). Evening performances in the week. Evening and matinee performances on weekends.
REMUNERATION: ¬£12.71 per hour (National Living Wage) for 100 hours of rehearsal and performance (inclusive of holiday pay).
ELIGIBILITY: Open audition for actors 18 years and older. Please contact us if you need any reasonable adjustments to audition.
AUDITION: Please submit a self tape of a monologue or soliloquy from any of Shakespeare's plays.
DEADLINE: Saturday 28th February at 11:59pm
EMAIL: shakespeareunstaged@gmail.com
CALLBACK: Saturday 28th March in central London

#juliuscaesar #shakespeare #secretshakespeare Secret Shakespeare #auditions #actors #acting #auditioning #readingabbeyruins Reading Abbey Quarter

items.text:
CASTING CALL: THE COLLECTOR (Short Film)

Production: Independent Short Film
Genre: Supernatural Horror / Psychological Thriller
Location: York, England
Shoot Dates: April 12th and 13th
Compensation: Unpaid. Catering provided. This project is intended as the beginning of an ongoing creative collaboration.

Synopsis:
The Collector explores the predatory nature of darkness and the dangerous misunderstanding of vulnerability. Innocence is not seen as purity, but as something to be consumed.

Roles Available:

Grace (Female, 40s) Lead
A composed, intelligent professional with a quiet but formidable presence. Calm, controlled, and shaped by survival.

Emma (Female, 14‚Äì15) Lead
Curious and isolated. Emotionally intuitive and observant. Becomes the focus of the Entity‚Äôs attention.

The Entity (Female) Supporting
A physical, unsettling presence of pale flesh and darkness. Strong physical performance required. Heavy makeup FX and sclera lenses involved.

David (Male, late 30s to 40s) Supporting
Emma‚Äôs father. Practical and protective, pushed into a terrifying supernatural confrontation.

Father Benedict (Male, 60s) Supporting
A frail but determined priest attempting an exorcism. Spiritually authoritative despite physical weakness.

Submission Requirements:
Please click on the Google forms link below to submit your answers: https://forms.gle/sbUWJAjRM8iJmJFMA
